fix(menu): vendor Menu & Items now writes to Supabase (was localStorage-only)

Root cause of "items not showing in student app even though canteen is online":
the vendor's Menu & Items tab persisted only to localStorage. Items never
reached menu_items, so /api/canteens/[id]/menu returned an empty list.

Changes:
- app/vendor/dashboard/page.tsx → VendorMenuView:
  * Now takes a session prop (Supabase access token).
  * GET /api/canteen/menu on mount populates state from DB.
  * POST /api/canteen/menu on Add Item.
  * PATCH /api/canteen/menu/[id] on Edit and on availability toggle.
  * DELETE /api/canteen/menu/[id] on Remove (with confirm).
  * Maps local Item shape (mealType / productionType / capacity / serveType)
    to DB shape (category / availability_type / quantity_per_slot or
    total_per_day / is_meal). Reverses on read.
  * Optimistic UI for toggle/delete with rollback on failure.
  * Loading + error states surfaced in the page header.
  * "Save Menu" button still arms the canteen ON gate
    (vendor_menu_configured flag) but the items themselves are now in DB.

- app/api/canteens/[id]/menu/route.ts: lowered cache from 60s to 5s
  (with 30s stale-while-revalidate) so vendor edits propagate to the user
  app within seconds. Egress overhead is negligible.

142/142 tests pass; production build clean.
